* The subclass of {@link SQLException} thrown when the SQLState class value is '0A' * ( the value is 'zero' A). * This indicates that the JDBC driver does not support an optional JDBC feature. * Optional JDBC features can fall into the fallowing categories: *

*

    *
  • no support for an optional feature *
  • no support for an optional overloaded method *
  • no support for an optional mode for a method. The mode for a method is *determined based on constants passed as parameter values to a method *
* * @since 1.6
